The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Three men were arrested at Calcutta airport on Wednesday morning after they arrived from Dubai on an Emirates flight on charges of tampering with their passports. Immigration officials said Mohammad Yasin, from Lucknow, and Mohammad Shahzada Ahmed, from Jammu, were charged with tampering with the expiry date of their passports. 

 bdul Jalil Kaden, from Kerala, was arrested when the officials found that a few pages from his passport were missing. The three will be produced in Barrackpore court on Thursday.

 Traffic along the Bondel Gate flyover and Rifle Range Road did not move for over an hour on Wednesday morning, as local residents organised a blockade demanding adequate supply of water. They alleged that the supply had been erratic for over a month. The blockade was withdrawn after the intervention of local political leaders and police.

 Manik Pyke, 32, was crushed to death after a log from a crane fell on him while unloading goods at the Kidderpore dock around 5am on Wednesday. Pyke, a dailywager from Mathurapur, South 24-Parganas, was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead.

 A Group D employee of the conservancy department of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation fell ill because of the heat on Wednesday afternoon. He was admitted to SSKM Hospital. 

 A gas balloon fitted with a small transmitter landed on Swamiji Nagar Playground, in Batanagar, on Tuesday night and set off panic among residents, who thought it to be a bomb. Police were informed and the area was cordoned off, but the balloon was found to have been flown by the meteorological department.

 Two persons were arrested in Barasat, on the northern fringes of the city, on Tuesday night on charges of possessing fake currency notes worth Rs 85,000. One of them is from Swarupnagar, close to the India-Bangladesh border in North 24-Parganas, and the other is a Baranagar resident, police said.

 Sunil Bhowmick, 21, drowned while taking a bath at the Dhakuria Lake on Tuesday evening. Members of the disaster management group fished out the body on Wednesday morning.

 The stepmother, father and uncle of Sujit Chakrabarty, 22, were arrested on Wednesday in connection with his death. Sujit was found dead on a road near his Barrackpore house, on the northern fringes of the city, on Tuesday morning. An unnatural death case has been lodged. The arrests followed a complaint lodged by Sujits maternal uncle.

